<br>
Seriously, I got together with another mage in DL the other day, and we were killing as fast, if not faster, than another group by us with a warrior, cleric, enchanter, blah blah blah.<br>
<br>
Two mages RULE!<br>
<br>
Side note: If you're talking about the best partner for a long period of time, (like if you and a friend are making characters) have him be a druid. Ports are niiiiiice, plus they heal (not so well later, but oh well) root/snare....they compliment our weaknesses rather nicely. <p><b><font size="1"><a target="new" href="http://eq.castersrealm.com/players/view_profile.asp?Id=60066">Balthemal </a><br>50th Mage</font></b></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ugoladus.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Goladus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Arch Mage</span><br>  Posts: 516<br> <font color=#333333>(10/9/01 4:35:22 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=308.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Partnering?</span><hr size=1> Partner for a mage?  Easier to list the classes that don't partner well.  Here's my list in a vague order of preference.<br>
<br>
